5 useful expression 





約束するときは、必ず少なくとも10分くらい余裕を持つようにしています。


When making plans, I always try to leave at least a 10-minute buffer just in case


A: "Are you the type who shows up right on time for plans?"
B: "Nah, I always try to leave at least a 10-minute buffer. You never know what might happen."


"How’s your seat? Comfortable?"
B: "Kinda... It’s one of those non-reserved seats with a reclining chair.
I’m worried if I lean back too much, I’ll bother the person behind me.
But if I don’t recline enough, it’s really uncomfortable.
It's so hard to find a good angle!"


